[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Code
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Reference implementations:** The following AWS sample resources demonstrate the patterns used in this recipe:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m >
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > - [`amazon-sagemaker-examples`](https://github.com/aws/amazon-sagemaker-examples): Official SageMaker examples including XGBoost, custom container patterns, and Processing jobs
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > - [AWS Step Functions Workflow Studio](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/step-functions/latest/dg/workflow-studio.html): For visually composing the nightly pipeline orchestration
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > - [Amazon QuickSight Workshops](https://catalog.workshops.aws/quicksight): Patterns for finance and operational dashboards over Athena and DynamoDB
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m <!-- TODO (TechWriter): N1. Verify all reference implementation links are still live during the pre-publication audit. -->
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Walkthrough
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 1: Build the per-claim feature table from open AR and historical remits.** The pipeline starts by joining the current open AR snapshot with the historical remit data so each open claim gets a feature vector that includes payer characteristics, claim type, financial amounts, and any relevant history. This is the unglamorous foundation; the quality of every downstream model depends on getting the features right.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION build_feature_table(open_ar_snapshot_path, remit_history_path, contract_data_path, output_path):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Load the current open AR. One row per claim that has been
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // submitted but not fully resolved (paid or written off).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     open_ar = read_parquet(open_ar_snapshot_path)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Required fields: claim_id, patient_id, payer_id, claim_type,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // submission_date, billed_amount, expected_reimbursement,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // primary_procedure_code, primary_diagnosis_code, place_of_service,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // current_status (submitted, denied, in_appeal, partially_paid).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Load the historical 835 remit data. Used both to compute timing
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // distributions in Step 2 and to back-fill features here (e.g.,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // a "this payer has slowed down by N days vs trailing 90-day average"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // feature for the open claims).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     remits = read_parquet(remit_history_path)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Required fields: claim_id, payer_id, payment_date, paid_amount,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // adjustment_codes, denial_codes, claim_status_code.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Load the contract data so we know contractual reimbursement rates,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // capitation schedules, and any payer-specific timing rules.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     contracts = read_parquet(contract_data_path)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Compute payer-level rolling features that will help the per-claim model.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     payer_features = compute_payer_rolling_features(remits, lookback_days = 90)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Includes: median days-to-remit (last 30/60/90 days), denial rate
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // (last 30/60/90 days), rework success rate, and recent trend in
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // each metric.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Compute claim-level features that combine payer behavior, claim
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // characteristics, and the patient's prior claim history.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     enriched = open_ar
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         .join(payer_features, on = payer_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         .join(contracts, on = (payer_id, claim_type))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         .with_column(days_outstanding = today() - submission_date)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         .with_column(prior_denials_for_patient =
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             lookup_prior_denials(remits, patient_id, lookback_days = 365))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         .with_column(claim_dollar_band = bucket(billed_amount,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                        breaks = [0, 500, 2000, 10000, 50000, infinity]))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Tag each claim with its current "branch" of the model.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // - clean: never denied, expected to pay normally
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // - reworked: was denied, reworked, awaiting payment
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // - in_appeal: currently appealed, on the long-tail timeline
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // - capitation: deterministic schedule, no statistical model
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     enriched = enriched.with_column(model_branch = derive_branch(current_status, claim_type))
